@name Developer Guide: Understanding Angular Filters
@description

Angular filters format data for display to the user. For example, when you apply the "currency"
filter to a data value of `1234.5678` it displays as: `$1,234.57`. 

In addition to formatting data, filters can also modify the DOM. This allows filters to handle
tasks such as conditionally applying CSS styles to filtered output.

The Angular framework provides a standard set of filters for common operations:

* {@link api/angular.filter.currency currency}
* {@link api/angular.filter.date date}
* {@link api/angular.filter.html html}
* {@link api/angular.filter.json json}
* {@link api/angular.filter.linky linky}
* {@link api/angular.filter.uppercase lowercase}
* {@link api/angular.filter.number number}
* {@link api/angular.filter.uppercase uppercase}


